# Debugging & triage

## Triage first

- Reproduce the failure reliably, characterize the symptom, and scope the blast
  radius before forming hypotheses. A bug you can't reproduce, you can't confirm fixed.

## Rule out environmental causes

- Before calling a hang, timeout, crash, flaky test, or build failure a regression, rule
  out machine contention (load averages; CPU-heavy or orphaned processes), external/infra
  state, and resource exhaustion.
- Reproduce in a clean environment and retry after contention clears. Extend timeouts only
  as a last resort with the reason documented.
- Never kill unrelated processes, including other agent sessions, without explicit
  authorization. Confirm a process is genuinely orphaned first, and report before/after evidence.
- For slow suites and subprocess harnesses, see `my-testing`.

## Method

- Test one hypothesis/variable at a time — unless deliberately running a
  `git bisect`-style search.
- Form a hypothesis → change one thing → observe → repeat. Don't shotgun several
  fixes at once and lose track of which one mattered.

## Running checks

- Linters/validators → `my-linting`. Tests → `my-testing`. Editor (Neovim) ops → `my-editor-neovim`.
